Frequently Asked Questions - ARC Raiders Item Guide

What items should I keep in ARC Raiders?

Keep all quest items, hideout project materials, and critical crafting materials like Metal Parts, Rubber Parts, Battery, Wires, ARC Alloy, Steel Spring, and Durable Cloth. Use our smart recommendation system to see specific guidance for each item.

What items should I sell in ARC Raiders?

Sell high-value items (2,000â‚¡+) with poor recycling efficiency, items with no crafting use, and duplicate materials you have in excess. Items like Ruined Accordion, Portable TV, Spotter Relay, and Torn Blanket are typically better to sell.

What is the raid recycling penalty in ARC Raiders?

Recycling during a raid returns only 50% of the normal materials. Always recycle in your hideout (Speranza) for full 100% material yields. Our guide shows both raid and hideout recycling outputs for every item.

How do I find quest items in ARC Raiders?

Use our search feature to find any quest item. All quest-required items are marked with "KEEP: Quests" badge and show exactly which quests need them and how many.

What materials are most important in ARC Raiders?

Metal Parts (needed for 200+ crafts), Rubber Parts (150+ uses), Wires (30+ uses), Battery (30+ uses), Steel Spring, Electrical Components, and ARC Alloy are critical materials. Our priority system highlights which materials to prioritize.

How much is each item worth in ARC Raiders?

Every item displays its sell value in credits (â‚¡). Values range from 50â‚¡ for basic materials to 5,500â‚¡ for rare components. Use our price guide to make informed sell decisions.

What can I craft with my materials in ARC Raiders?

Search any material to see all crafting recipes that use it. Our database includes Workbench, Gunsmith, Gear Bench, Medical Lab, Explosives Station, Utility Station, and Refiner recipes.

Which items recycle into Metal Parts?

Broken Flashlight (6x), Damaged Heat Sink (6x), many mechanical and technological items. Use the "Safe to Recycle" filter and look for recycling information to find Metal Parts sources.

Is this ARC Raiders guide updated?

Yes! Updated to V1.3.1 (Nov 15, 2025) with the latest item data from Embark Studios' ARC Raiders. We sync daily with the official arcraiders-data repository.
